    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27a.21-22_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">21</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    Martin Rich
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>5/12/59.</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Niehart<sic>Neihardt</sic>:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Please do forgive me for my thoughtlessness, but in my own anxiety to get things moving on this project I have been guilty of neglect in not considering that you would of course want to know something more about me than my earnest desire to exploit your book to our mutual benefit.</p>
                
                <p>I am a young man (35) with a show business background that goes back to the age of six, when I performed <del>k</del><add>i</add>n vaudville with my parents.</p>
                
                <p>Presently I am engaged as an assistant director on the feature film, "Anniversary Waltz", immediately after which I will function as Associate Producer on an Independent production of the life of "Pretty Boy Floyd".</p>
                
                <p>The ten years leading up to this present have seen me in all phases of <hi rend="caps">T.V.</hi> and Motion Picture work and in all types of projects of 10 second commercial spots to feature length pictures.... ( I am not an agent).</p>
                
                <p>My interest in your book is from the aspect of doing something the likes of which has not been done and needs to be, and to advance my own caree r.</p>
                
                <p>The successful completion of the project which I outlined to you, Sir, will put me on a level with any of the top producers in the field.</p>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27a.21-22_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="authorial">2.</fw>
                <fw type="curatorial">22</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    Martin Rich
                </fw>
                
                <p>Naturally I find this aspect very desirable but the prospects of success as a producer alone isn't the goal I seek. It is in being a part of a project that I feel will have some value...other than pure so-called entertainment, and which will lead to other projects which can be considered perhaps as culturally u plifting but will retain the elements of entertainment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Looking forward to your continuing interest in the future of our project is</salute>
                
                    <signed>Martin Rich</signed>
                    <signed>Martin Rich.</signed>
                
                    <note>em/mr</note>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
